English:
The Prince Albert has laid before Parliament a bold proposal: to host an unprecedented international exhibition celebrating the industrial achievements of all nations. This 'Great Exhibition' would require significant investment to construct a massive glass and iron structure in Hyde Park - already dubbed the 'Crystal Palace' by Punch magazine.

Proponents argue this showcase would cement our position as the world's leading industrial power and generate substantial revenue from the millions of expected visitors. The exhibition would display the finest achievements in manufacturing, engineering, and the arts from across the globe.

However, some MPs express concern over the substantial initial costs. Shall we fund this grand vision of British ingenuity and industrial might?;;;;;;;;;;;;;
